subSubSection.paragraph:
Status and Conservation.
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Cameratrap imaging rates for this species suggest moderately high local abundancesin primary lower montane forests of the upper Kikori River catchment. The Elegant Water Rat appears to be absent from the Purari River catchment (immediately east of the Kikori River catchment) which has been intensive surveyed from sea level to 1500 m, most recently including camera trapping and analysis of large owl pellet accumulations. The apparent elevationalshift between eastern and western populations might reflect contrasting patterns of competition—on the south-eastern Papuan Peninsula the Elegant Water Rat is replaced at higher elevations by the Small Water Rat (
L. paulus
) but there is no other species at lower elevation; in the Kikori and Strickland River catchments the elevational limits of the Elegant Water Rat are bracketed below, by records of the Fly River Water Rat (
L. signatus
) and above, by records of Ernst Mayr’s Water Rat (
L. ernstmayri
). There are no known instances of local sympatry of two species of 
Leptomys
.
